prompt.preamble:
We are testing a system for understanding people's interest in reading different kinds of online articles.
For example, you might be interested in articles about some topics, but not about others.
prompt.task_description: your preferences of what kinds of online articles you would like to read
prompt.final: In the final part of the study, you will give feedback on a test set of article headline and descriptions, which will enable us to see how well a chatbot reading your responses has learned what you like and dislike.
prompt.evaluation: Please indicate whether you would like to read the following articles: "yes" if you would, "no" if you would not.

conversation_history.message: Question: Can you tell me about any specific themes, genres, or subjects that you find particularly engaging or intriguing in online articles?
issues having to do with civil rights and racial justice
Question: Besides civil rights and racial justice, are there any other topics such as technology, health, environment, or entertainment that you enjoy reading about in online articles?
technology, health
Question: Are there any specific areas within technology and health that you are particularly interested in, or do you enjoy reading about other topics such as travel, food, or sports?
travel, food
Question: Apart from the topics you've mentioned, do you also find interest in areas like arts, culture, fashion, or personal development when reading online articles?
yes all of the above
Question: Do you also enjoy reading about topics related to personal finance, education, or science in online articles?
education, science
Question: In addition to the topics you've mentioned, do you also find interest in reading about lifestyle, home decor, gardening, or DIY projects in online articles?
home decor, lifestyle
Question: Do you also find interest in reading about topics related to politics, history, philosophy, or psychology in online articles?
yes all of the above
Question: Are there any specific authors, publications, or styles of writing that you particularly enjoy or find engaging when reading online articles?
not particularly

Question: Do you have any preferences when it comes to the length, complexity, or format of the online articles you read? For example, do you prefer short, concise articles or long, in-depth ones? Do you enjoy listicles, how-to guides, opinion pieces, research studies, or news reports?
depends, i like everything but varies on my mood and present interests

Question: Can you share if there are any specific times or situations when you prefer to read certain types of articles? For example, do you enjoy reading lighter topics like entertainment or lifestyle during your leisure time, or do you prefer to read more serious topics like politics or science during your work breaks?
not really, i am open to reading anything whenever
Question: Can you tell me about any specific online platforms or websites where you usually prefer to read these articles? And why do you prefer these sources?
i like the new york times, i think it has a good variety of stuff
Question: Can you tell me about any specific online articles that have left a strong impression on you recently? What was the topic, and what about it made it memorable or impactful for you?
not really, i can't remember anything off the top of my head

Question: Can you tell me about any online articles that have challenged your views or made you think differently about a certain topic? What was the article about and why did it have such an impact on you?
not off the top of my head
Question: Can you tell me about any online articles that you've found particularly useful or informative? What was the topic, and how did it benefit you in your personal or professional life?

i did read this article about how they are making developments in making it such that blind people could be transmitted the sound vibrations based on a partner's face to be able to detect, or have some sense of what their face looks like. I thought this was very interesting

Question: Can you tell me about any online articles that have sparked your curiosity or led you to further research or explore a topic? What was the article about and what new interests or hobbies did it inspire?
what i just said
Question: Can you tell me about any online articles that have emotionally moved you or deeply resonated with you? What was the topic, and why did it have such a profound effect on you?
can't remember off the top of my head
Question: Can you tell me about any online articles that have surprised you or taught you something you didn't expect? What was the topic, and why was it surprising or unexpected?
not particularly
